      'biography1':"  When religion was destroyed, when God had to incarnate. Insults of sadhus, oppression, destruction of religion started on this earth. Then the whole earth became frightened like a cow. At that time, Lord Shiva was forced to take on the role of avatar. Therefore, Renukacharya was incarnated through the pancha mouth of Shiva, which is part of Shiva. At that time Lord Shiva incarnated from Somalinga in Kollapaki (Andhra Pradesh) and came to this planet. From there onwards his name became Jagatguru Revanasiddheshwar. Jagatguru disguised himself as saffron and began to tell people the meaning of Shivsandesh, Shivattva and Shivnama. He has been incarnated in every age. He came around India in a mobile form, moving around 56 parts.At that time Shri Mahalakshmi gave Kalkutta poison to every Siddha, but no one could take it. So Mahalakshmi banned all Siddhas. After learning this, Revanasiddha got rid of all Siddhas by drinking the terrible Kalkut poison. At that time all Siddhas cheered him. Later he visited Chinchali Mayakka and settled in Siddhanal village and guided the people there in Shivanama. Similarly Ravana of Lanka wanted. That 7 crore lingas should be worshiped once but due to his death it remained insufficient, 4 crore lingas were created by the hands of Ravana. 3 crore lingas would have remained. When Ravana's brother Bibhishan remembered Jagatguru Revanasiddheshwar, Revanasiddheva went and established three crore lingas in the city of Lanka. And Ravana's wish was fulfilled. While he was wandering around performing many such divine miracles, Shri Biroba gave Lord Halmat Guru bodh. Thus Halmat Dharma was saved. Also came from Kailasa and guided Sri Shiva-Padmagonda.\n  From there onwards, Jagatguru traveled around 56 countries for fourteen hundred years and came to Bhuyar and became famous in Ghor Aran. (Swanalgi) Mudagonda and Sugladevi were blessed with a son by the Solapur Shiv Devotee couple, thus Maha Shivayogi Siddha Rameshwar, an incarnation of Shiva, was born. Jagatguru communicated by traveling all over the world. He became adhikakhya of many Shiv Tattvas. Humanity, tolerance, respect and unity were combined on this earth. Also re-created religion. Jagatguru Revanasiddevar gave the world valuable knowledge of Sivanam, Siva-tattva, and Siva-adoration and finally united in Somalinga at Kollapaki.\n\n\nThis information is about\nSri Bargalsiddha Mahatme Granth\nAuthor - Sri Adveppa Somutte (Wadiyar)\nPoet, Poet, Writer Kannada and Marathi.",
      'biography2':"  In the Satya Yuga, Shri Biroba was born at Chandanagiri on the banks of the Krishna River to father Shri Bal Bharamdev and mother Ganga Soravanti. (believed to have been born from above) Nagari Pattan Narada was Sri Biroba's paternal uncle. Biroba was severely tortured by Narada during his childhood. As soon as the demon was sent, the baby Biroba was taken to the forest and left to be nursed. Narada wanted the demon to destroy them. Because he was incarnate, the demons could not kill him. After leaving the cradle in Kudalinandan forest, they returned. Sri Ekva Sri Maivva living in Mandangiri came to Kudlinandan forest with two sisters grazing goats when they saw the cradle. He picked up the cradle and took it home with him. Those two sisters took care of Sri Birudeva with great affection. He brought it up as a child. After Sri Biroba reached marriageable age, he won the daughter of Sri Narad of Nagripattan and married Kan Kamavati. Narada had tortured them a lot. In his mature age Sri Biroba went to Sarvajan Mungi Paithan with Ekva and Maivva devachasakha Bafana communicating with him. He cured the illness of Sri Kesuraya there. A weapon named Panchadangi, Vayughanghal Kashiling was obtained from the king to kill the demon. Sri Devachasakha Bafana dedicated himself to the manufacture of that weapon by the river Godavari. He cured the illness of Sri Kesuraya there. A weapon named Panchadangi, Vayughanghal Kashiling was obtained from the king to kill the demon. Sri Devachasakha Bafana dedicated himself to the manufacture of that weapon by the river Godavari. He cured the illness of Sri Kesuraya there. A weapon named Panchadangi, Vayughanghal Kashiling was obtained from the king to kill the demon. Sri Devachasakha Bafana dedicated himself to the manufacture of that weapon by the river Godavari. Later, Birudevani came to Nagthan (District Bijapur) doing Sanchar. There she offered up Nagdev. The created weapon defeated the demons like Kwanesura, Bagi-Bankasura, Shigi-Shinkhasura, Jogasura, Kopasura, Kanpesura, etc. And freed the people from fear. Chinchali Raibag, Distt. Belgaum Ekva and Maivva started to cry. This village became a place of pilgrimage. Even today, numerous devotees from India gather at Chinchali on Navanna Purnimas. It is a major pilgrimage site of the Halmat religion. After that Mr. Biroba kept his wife Kan Kamavati in Arewadi. They settled there permanently. He then killed Garjanasura. He took the name Gajlingeshwar there and freed many people from trouble. Offered abhaydan to the Rishi Muni there. He bestowed the honorific name “Nirvaneshwar” on Sri Biroba. The place where Garjanasura was killed. The place is called Ghodegiri (in the vicinity of Ghodegiri one of Biroba's devotees called Nirvaneshwar Rishi passed away) where Shri Biroba did severe penance for twelve years. Finally, he got a boon from Shiva Parvati and spent twenty-four years in penance at Don Heggeri (now Donaj, Mangalvedha). It was there that he and Mahalingaraya met in Donaj Lake. There are thousands of temples all over India sanctified by the presence of Shri Biroba Deva. Bijapur Dist. Bijapur, Sri Karesiddha-Biroba Mandir, Kwannur, T. Jamkhandi, Dist. Bagalkot, Sri Gajlingeshwar and Nirvaneshwar Mandir Ghodegiri Dongar Hukkeri, Dist. Belgaon. Sri Banknath – Biroba Mandir, Bagi, Tt. Raibag, Distt. Belgaon. Sri Kurudilinga-Birappa Temple, Eksamba, T. Chikkodi, Dist. Belgaon, Sri Shidiyan Siddha Mandir, Shirdhon, Tt. Indi, Distt. Bijapur, Shree Karsiddha Mandir, Alkhanur Raibag District Belgaum Sri Kashiling Biroba and Kamavati Mandir, Arewadi, Tt. Kavthemahankal Dist. Sangli Sri Santosha-Biroba Mandir Pangri and Takewadi Man, Dist. Satara Shree Vitthal-Birdev Mandir Pattan Kodoli, Hatkanangle Dist. Kolhapur Shree Dhikakhan-Biroba Mandir, Vashi Karveer, Dist. Kolhapur Shree Mursiddh Mandir Murgundi Athani, Distt. Belgaum Sri Rayavannur-Biroba Mandir Vannur Distt. Mangalvedha, Solapur Shree Birudev Mandir Baramati Distt. Pun