      'biography3':"In Satya Yuga, Shri Mahalingaraya was born to (King) Tukapparaya Sati Amritbai in Bhimthadi, Bilwad i.e. present day Baramati district. Happened in Pune. (Bhimthadi, Bilwad Baramati are all the names of the same place.) In his childhood, along with his elder brother Zakaraya, he performed many miracles and relieved the sufferings of the people. Once, when there was a severe drought, he left Baramati with his father Tukapparaya and cousin Somraya and cousin Kanubai brother Jakobaraya and came to Kharsundis from their relative village to graze cows and stay at Kanheri. Stayed there for a few days. During the stay, the first drawn edge of the cowhides of their cows became square katta as soon as they left it on the sand. While carrying the cows ahead, Somraya asked his brother “what will happen to the milk katya” Sri Tukapparaya replied – Hereafter the village named Khar+sundi Kharsundi will be famous. This place will be famous as the famous place of our Guru Sonarisiddha (Kaalbhairava). Having said this, Tukapparaya started walking along the banks of Mana river along with his brother. Shri Mahalingaraya was performing miracles with him. Next they came to the place where the Man river meets the Bhima river (Ozhewadi). Then they came to Umbaraj after grazing cows. (Umblethana) He lived there for more than a decade. People in that area considered him as Lord. Sri Tukapparaya alias Revappa fought with the evil Berda. He shot himself with an arrow so that his body would not fall into their hands and become impure. That was their end. His samadhi temple at Umbaraj is on a grand scale. Next they came to the place where the Man river meets the Bhima river (Ozhewadi). Then they came to Umbaraj after grazing cows. (Umblethana) He lived there for more than a decade. People in that area considered him as Lord. Sri Tukapparaya alias Revappa fought with the evil Berda. He shot himself with an arrow so that his body would not fall into their hands and become impure. That was their end. His samadhi temple at Umbaraj is on a grand scale. Next they came to the place where the Man river meets the Bhima river (Ozhewadi). Then they came to Umbaraj after grazing cows. (Umblethana) He lived there for more than a decade. People in that area considered him as Lord. Sri Tukapparaya alias Revappa fought with the evil Berda. He shot himself with an arrow so that his body would not fall into their hands and become impure. That was their end. His samadhi temple at Umbaraj is on a grand scale. Shri Mahalingaraya along with his cousin Somraya cousin Kanubai Bhau Jakobaraya proceeded on his journey. They traveled through Bhandarkavatha, Seena Telgaon, Solapur (Salerhatti), Boramani, Hiragubbi, (Amritkund), Chitgubbi (Chendkapur), Bhalgubbi (Bhalki), Nithur, Nilanga, Ganginadu (Gangakhed), Gaurinadu (Garbhagiri Hills), Halhavali Nadu (Harishchandra Hills). ), after arriving at Sal Bidrinadu (area of ​​Satmala Hills), he stayed in Shadbaba Hills (Satmala Hills). He stayed there for twelve years. During this period he learned esoteric knowledge from Sri Guru Sonari Siddha. Musical instruments (drums, kaitals, and fifty-two bidras) from Parameshwara came to the state of Halli Hanab from Mount Kailash. He accepted. That stuff was lying there for a long time. But no one could touch them. The toucher is consumed. But as all these were incarnations of the Lord, they had no difficulty in accepting these instruments. He performed many religious rituals while living in that area. He also built a village called 'Harnapur Pattan' in that area. A lake named Kamthan was dug and built in another area. Homa, Havan and religious rituals were performed at Haranapur. He made the people of that area happy and satisfied. Next he took twenty four thousand troops with himself. He proceeded to Umblethana (Umbaraj) to exterminate the evil Berads. When he came to Umbaraj by going floor to floor, he completed his dream. After the death of Berdas, he built a “Rudrakatta” in front of the Samadhi temple of his father Tukobarai alias Revappa. Sri Tukapparaya's right to prophesy has been handed down by family tradition in the family of certain devotees. Millions of people in Maharashtra and Karnataka have faith in this prediction. From Umble Thana Shri Mahalingaraya sent his brother Shri Jakobaraya to settle at Yenki He himself met his Guru Shri Biroba in the lake of Don Heggeri (Donaj) with devotion. He also established his Guru's Math at Shigimath (Shirdon). Sri Mahalingarayan worshiped the Guru eternally in that Math. At the same time, he had collected the milk of a tigress from Limbal mountain and offered it to the Guru. The name Huljanti came into circulation after Mahalingaraya gave the name 'Huljanti' to the village Jinti Narayanpur in memory of that tigress. That is what the current “Halmat religions” are all about. During the residence of Shri Biroba in Shirdon, Shri Mahalingaraya brought water untouched by frogs and flowers untouched by animals from Satyachi Pandurkoti and offered them to Shri Guru. He also freed many convicts from Pandurkoti. Devgonda Patil of Bettengiri conducted a grand celebration (hubb) of Sri Karesiddha at Kwannur. Sri Mahalingaraya was invited to the festival. In that festival, Shri Mahalingaraya performed many divine miracles and left everyone stunned. At the time of the festival, Sri Mahalingaraya became secret in the Agni Kunda. Seeing that he appeared safely at Mundganur, the Three Kosavar region, many Kutilsiddhas surrendered to him. It was during this period that Shri Biroba lived in Kshetra Shirdon. Sri Mahalingaraya respectfully brought him to the present area of ​​Hunnur (Gaurimath) and settled there. From there, Shri Biroba, Mahalingaraya visited twelve Jyotirlingas and many holy tirthas, he laid 56 countries under his feet, traveled everywhere, removed the problems of the people and devotees, banished the wicked and protected the nobles. Bhakti Bhava was flourished everywhere. Enlightened the ignorant. The siddhas were saved, the mumukshas were given salvation. Shri Biroba resided in Shri Kshetra Hunnur. Whereas Sri Mahalingaraya resided at Kshetra Huljanti\n\n\nBibliography Sri Bargalsiddha Mahatme\nComposed by poet-Adveppa Maharaya Wadiyar Sukshetra Huljantih\nMangalvedha Distt. Solapur",
      'biography4':"Zakaraya and Mahalingaraya were born to King Tukapparaya and Sati Amritabai in Baramati Pattana during Satya Yuga. The little Pani Jatjyot Bals performed many divine miracles and showed the glory of their incarnational work to the city of Baramati. After the drought, they stayed for some time in Umblithana carrying cows. Due to visible wounds, his body was left to boil. Later, Bhillal Somarai took care of his nephews with affection. Due to the grace of Guru Sonar Siddha, he came to Umblithana after traveling back with Shivasthan (Dhol-Kaital) from Kailas. As promised to his father, he performed the sightings and tied Rudra Katta to Umblithana, while returning, he met Guru-Bharamdev and his disciple Zakaraya in Bhima river. Later, the marriage ceremony of Zakaraya and Mahalingaraya was performed with great pomp. One day Shilgonda Honmane Patil of Sohale village sent an invitation to his son-in-law-Zakaraya to come to Sohale village for the festival of Diwali. Similarly, Jambunil Zakaraya marched through Ambari on the orders of his mother Kanubai accompanied by his chief Motilal Savkar. While Sohale is going to the village, 18 bhar instruments are playing. When he crossed the river Bhima from Umblethana to Sara Lavajma, he came to Telgaon, Kusur, Vadapur Batwate and Yenki, Guru Bharamdev of Jambunil Jakaraya came to Shive of the village from Yenki. Zechariah began to ask. How many days have passed since I met Zakaraya, when will my puja come? On hearing this, Zakaray promised the Guru that he would come back and worship in four or five days. When Zakaraya went to Sohale village, his religious wife Sati Bakabai had already gone to Sohale village for Dussehra festival. After Jakoba came to Sohale village, he created a big disturbance in the village. The road greeted them with rangolis and sweets. Stayed there for many days. Zakaraya is due to devotion to Guru, people's diseases, their sufferings. Vazenla's son, milking cows and buffaloes started performing divine miracles. At that time many days passed, but they did not remember to go to Yenki. This Arava accumulated knowledge happened to Guru Bharamdev who maddened Zakaraya by chanting mantras (chap) to remind him of the dark middle night. Then Zakaraya got up and started running, when Zakaraya Yenki and Sohale came to Shive village, Motilal Savkar, Pradhan, Sati Bakabai, Shilgonda Honmane Patil all came running behind him. At that time, as soon as Shiva of Yenki village got his feet, he went crazy and all the people started asking. what happened At that time Zakaraya said that the order of Guru Bharamdev has come. All of you should go back to Gad Yenki Math. But I can't come. Similarly give leave to 24 thousand troops. Motilal Savkar and tell him that your job is over. Saying this, Zakaraya and Bakabai went to the village to worship the Guru. Every morning they used to take water from the river Bhima early in the morning. At that time, Gurubharamdev was coming from Chandanagiri and worshiping his beloved disciple Zakaraya. No one knew it was coming. But one day something different happened, while doing the puja of Guru Bharamdev, a Guru Rakhi boy first. And he told the villagers that way. When all the villagers came outside the village to see Guru Bharamdev, Bharamdev made them faint. Zechariah was saddened to see this. Why keep the sheep all day? Keep these fainting people? Why worship the service of the Guru? Why should I eat with my stomach? Because Sati Bakabai had gone to Savale village to give birth. Tuljabhavani Mata, the mother of the world, took care of her beloved baby. She came to the fort with the Khandoba of Bale village. Khandoba kept the sheep. Bhawani Mata cooked while Zakaraya did the puja. After the passage of three days, Guru Bharamdev's heart melted and told Zakaraya, child, your devotion to Guru is great. For Gad Yenki Village Gad Yenki Village came to its former status as soon as Jambunil Zakaraya offered his unborn child to his Guru. And they began to devote themselves to Gadayenki Math. Even today it is a revered place of Halmat. Zakaraya, Gurubharamdev, Khandoba, Tuljabhavani, Sati Bakabai have grace over this village. Chaitrapurnima is a 4-day journey. And people become blessed by seeing Zachariah. During the yatra, religious rituals such as visitation of palanquin, sabina, bhakanuk, homa, taat etc. are performed. We should take darshan of this venerable elder brother of Mahalingaraya and take blessings.\n\n\nInformation Collection\nSri Zakaraya Ovikar Mandal\nSector-Yenki, Tt. Mohol, Solapur\nShaheer – Kumar Gaurappa Koli\nand Sri-Shivaji Gund (Patil) – Lead Singers",
      'biography5':"In this world, when the Asuri Shakti took hold, our gods and goddesses had to incarnate in order to protect the religion in the world. Just as the god Biroba killed the demon Kwanesura and freed the earth from fear, so Mayava killed the demon Kil-Katta and freed the people from fear. Akka Ekva and Akka Maivva, two sisters living in Mandangiri town, took home the cradle of the baby Biroba found in Kudlinandan forest. This little baby was cared for with great affection and love. Later, after Birudev grew up, his marriage ceremony with Kan Kamavati took place. Further, while the Avatar was working, Akka Ekavva and Maivva came to Chinchani city in a delusion and killed the visible Kill and Katt Daitya who became frenzied and got a boon from the deity and stayed there forever in the palace of Hirabai where Nandu started and began to benefit the devotees. This goddess resides in all caste religions and is famous as the goddess who answers the call of the devotee. Lakhs of devotees from the states of Andhra, Karnataka, Maharashtra, Goa take darshan of the goddess and seek happiness for their families, children and Prapancha. However, we should visit this place of God at least once, see the Yatra and take darshan and take blessings. (Chinchli, Dist.- Raibag, Dist.- Belgaon)\n\n\nInformation Collection\n(Archive)",
      'introduction':"Shri Farande Maharaj\n\n(Shri Shiva-Parvati-created religion)\n\n\n Many religions were created in this world. Some religions are composed. In that, the religion created by Shiva-Parvati is 'Sri Halmat'. The foundation of Halmat Dharma was actually laid by Shiva-Parvati in the form of Sati-Muddavva Pati Muddgaunda. Shiv-Parvati actually did the work of lighting up this earth through Halmata. Shree Halmata has done a great job of saving or bringing them on the path from the darkness that has come to human religion, the desecration of gods and goddesses due to blind tendencies, and the downfall of the human race due to ignorance. Basically, the word 'Halumatha' has emerged from Kannada language itself, to explain, Halu means milk thought, a stream of thought. \n\n  People who have a flow of thought like holy milk are the same for all of us. Those who live like sacred milk and empty their stomachs on it are all followers of the original Satya Halamat. Among them, Sati Muddavva Muddagounda Jagatguru Revanasiddha, Sadguru-Biroba disciple Mahalingaraya Devi Mayakka Bijjargi, Bullappa Khasagi-Bargalsiddha, Siddha-Suryappa Yenki-Zakaraya, Mayappa-Banchappa, Sri Vitthal, all of whom became heroes in Halmata. Abolished, propagated and propagated with renewed vigour. While we are all followers of the religion created by Shiva and Parvati, our condition is disappearing in this Kali Yuga and we all have forgotten about it.\n\n Therefore, through our 'Sri Halmat Sampradaya' group, we are working to spread and promote it, not only this family, but we all should spread and spread this true Halmat and know how our history is. Organizational strength will be useful for that. Therefore, it is a selfish expectation of the group and our family that we should spread Halmat religion like other religions and give our contribution.\n\n\n– Sri Farande Maharaj Sampradaya Parivar\n(State of Maharashtra and Karnataka)",
      
